<font color="#FF0000">GOOD MORNING, SUPER PROTESTOR</font><br>
<tt>Thu Nov  6  6:23:52 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
You will never get anywhere with the pathological personality behind &quot;spatz, cybergook, it, or whatever.&quot; Just as there are people who steadfastly and really believe that they are Napoleon, &quot;it&quot; believes that &quot;it&quot; is some form of &quot;Super Protestor&quot;, and no one will ever get around behind it and have any form of civil, intellectual dialog with this individual, ever.<br><br>
Like people who believe they are Napoleon, and reside at asylums for the insane, &quot;it&quot; is very much insane also. If you take the time to go through this whole site, as Cook and I and many others have done, the litany and techniques are repetitious. Just look at how many people have pegged &quot;it&quot; as a phoney, and worse, and it just never works. People have been complaining about &quot;its&quot; foul mouth, inconsistancy, and general insulting nature since the dawn of this site, and nothing has worked with anyone.<br><br>
The reason why nothing works is that it just can't. Like the insane whose reality is Napoleon, Super Protestor is the personality of a very insane mind.<br><br>
Mom of WEBTV is right in her assertion that you have to ignore this person. That is one classic way of managing insanity such as this. <br><br>
Another way to manage this personality is to lie and completely agree with this person on everything, even going so far as to say they should erect a statue in his honor for his heroic efforts, etc., etc. This technique keeps everything nice and calm.<br><br>
&quot;Good morning, Super Protestor, have a nice night lying on the tracks? Really, well, that's a shame. Here, take your pills and I'll be back later and you can tell me everything. Good morning Napoleon, how was Waterloo last night?, Really, that's a shame............&quot; <br><br>
If you personally detatch yourself from the issues of Super Protestor, you can pull off the &quot;ignore it&quot; or &quot;patronize it&quot; survival techniques and not compromise yourself.<br><br>
However, once they get at you, they will relentlessly and cleverly screw with your mind, consider everything they have said or done in the past as unimportant, and start the whole process all over again. This is not the mind of a normal person with a conscience, morals, ethics, or anything else in the control zone which helps to define a normal person. This is a mind which is missing big important pieces. <br><br>
When a personality such as this bumps into reality, as Super Protestor does here, the extent of the fantasy becomes very evident. In order to protect the fantasy, he has to resort to every trick in the book, including foul language, lying, deceit, unprovoked attack, and the contents of the Paris sewer, to maintain the artificial status and self esteem he needs to &quot;survive&quot;.<br><br>
Now you ask, how does a person such as this survive in the real world? Very easily. Some are only partially disconnected, and have skills that keep them afloat. He comes here for a fix now and then, because we are a predictable source of food for his self esteem. &quot;Look at what I told them, etc.&quot;<br><br>
Super Protestor, cybergook, &quot;it&quot;, or whatever, will probably come screaming out of the corner like a banshee when it reads this, or ignore it and go off and start another thread thinking everyone will forget what has transpired here, again. Go back up the threads and you will see the pattern repeat itself, over and over.<br><br>
It has taken me a while to understand all this. Now that I do, and I realize that &quot;its&quot; words are the product of a dimented mind, &quot;its&quot; insults, foul language, and crude deportment are not important in my life. It is clear that &quot;it&quot; is not capable of rational discussion in any way, though some of it is thinly and cleverly disguised as such. <br><br>
&quot;Good morning, Super Protestor, remember when you lied on the tracks? I sure would like to hear that stort again. It is real exciting. Me? I was a bad boy in Vietnam, but lets hear that story of yours again....please....&quot;<br><br>
Its a sick world out there folks, and we have a little corner of it! Pathetic, isn't it!<br><br>

